metadata.name: Onna-Bugeisha 女武芸者
metadata.description:
Onna-Bugeisha 女武芸者is a term referring to female warriors in pre-modern Japan. These women fought in battle alongside samurai men.They were members of the bushi (samurai) class in feudal Japan and were trained in the use of weapons to protect their household, family, and honour in times of war.They also have an important presence in
